        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-16T16:18:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-16T16:18:00-05:00" n="192"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d192">
                <head>192. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Central Intelligence Agency</gloss>
                    to <gloss type="to">Operation <gloss target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss>
                        Headquarters in Florida</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d192fn1">Source: Central Intelligence Agency,
                        Job 79–01025A, Box 9, Folder 2. Secret; Priority; RYBAT; <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss>. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_WFHSW1">Wisner</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1954-06-16T21:18:00+00:00">June 16, 1954, 2118Z</date>.</dateline>
                <p>05144. Ref: GUAT 857.<note n="2" xml:id="d192fn2">Not printed. (Ibid., Box 11,
                        Folder 4)</note>
                </p>
                <p>We question strongly proposal para 1 reference that Campesinos be enjoined kill
                    Guardia Civil, etc. This amounts to incitement civil war and large-scale blood
                    letting thus fouling <persName corresp="#p_CJH1">Calligeris</persName> pitch and
                    discrediting his movement as terrorist and irresponsible outfit willing
                    sacrifice innocent lives. An acceptable line would be enjoin Campesinos and
                    others defend and protect themselves and other anti-Communists who are being
                    hunted down in frantic Communist effort save tottering regime.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
